properties.areaDesc: Southern Brevard County; Okeechobee; Martin; Osceola; St. Lucie; Indian River
properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 7 at 1:16AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
At 110 AM EST, radar indicated a squall line of strong to severe
thunderstorms from near Mosquito Lagoon to Kenansville, and was
moving east at 50 to 60 mph.

Strong to damaging wind gusts of 50 to 60 mph are expected with this
line as it moves across all of Brevard County and rural central and
southern Osceola County through 3 AM, across the Treasure Coast
counties of Indian river, Saint Lucie and Martin, as well as the
Lake Okeechobee region from 3 AM, or a little earlier, through 5 AM.

A brief isolated tornado is still possible! Listen for possible
additional Severe Weather Warnings and move to safe shelter if one
is issued for your location!

A Tornado Watch continues for Brevard, Osceola, Okeechobee, and
Indian River Counties through 3 AM.

NWSheadline: Squall Line Entering Brevard and central Osceola Counties Will Reach the Lake Okeechobee and Treasure Coast Regions Later This Morning
